## Change 1 — Extract `CreateConfirmButton` + add `VerticalContentAlignment`

**File:** `src/VisualRelay.App/App.axaml.cs`

1. Add a new `internal static` factory method after the closing `}` of `ShowConfirmationAsync` and before the closing `}` of the `App` class (i.e., after line 141):

```csharp
internal static Button CreateConfirmButton(string confirmLabel) =>
    new Button
    {
        Content = confirmLabel,
        MinWidth = 80,
        Padding = new Thickness(12, 0),
        Height = 32,
        HorizontalContentAlignment = Avalonia.Layout.HorizontalAlignment.Center,
        VerticalContentAlignment = Avalonia.Layout.VerticalAlignment.Center
    };
```

2. In `ShowConfirmationAsync`, replace the inline confirm-button construction (lines 113–122) with a single call to the factory:

```csharp
CreateConfirmButton(confirmLabel)
```

The retrieval `confirmBtn = (Button)buttons.Children[1]` (line 133) continues to work because the factory returns the same `Button` type, still the second child of the StackPanel.

## Change 2 — New structural-guard test

**File:** `+tests/VisualRelay.Tests/ConfirmationDialogButtonAlignmentTests.cs`

A new file containing one test class with one `[AvaloniaFact]`, following the pattern of `TaskDetailRemoveButtonLayoutTests` (structural guard on a located control, `[Collection("Headless")]`). No headless window needed — the test calls `App.CreateConfirmButton` directly.

```csharp
using Avalonia;
using Avalonia.Controls;
using Avalonia.Layout;
using VisualRelay.App;

namespace VisualRelay.Tests;

/// <summary>
/// Structural guard: the shared confirmation-dialog confirm button
/// (built by <see cref="App.CreateConfirmButton"/>) must vertically
/// center its label so it matches the adjacent Cancel button.
/// </summary>
[Collection("Headless")]
public sealed class ConfirmationDialogButtonAlignmentTests
{
    [AvaloniaFact]
    public void CreateConfirmButton_VerticallyCentersLabel_AndPreservesExistingLayout()
    {
        var button = App.CreateConfirmButton("Rewrite and Replace");

        // The fix: vertical content alignment must be Center.
        Assert.Equal(
            VerticalAlignment.Center,
            button.VerticalContentAlignment);

        // Existing properties must be preserved untouched.
        Assert.Equal(
            HorizontalAlignment.Center,
            button.HorizontalContentAlignment);
        Assert.Equal(32.0, button.Height);
        Assert.Equal(80.0, button.MinWidth);
        Assert.Equal(new Thickness(12, 0), button.Padding);
        Assert.Equal("Rewrite and Replace", button.Content as string);
    }
}
```

