1. Run `./visual-relay check` — confirms build + all tests + formatting pass.
2. The new test verifies `VerticalContentAlignment == Center` — fails before the fix, passes after.
3. Existing confirmation tests (`RewriteMutualExclusionTests.RewriteConfirmation_UsesRewriteAndReplaceConfirmLabel`, `AddAttachmentsVisibilityTests.RemoveAttachment_UsesDeleteConfirmLabel`) stay green — they mock `ShowConfirmationAsync` at the delegate level and never touch the dialog construction.
4. The `SplitGuardVerificationTests.Headless` reflection guard passes — the new test class carries `[Collection("Headless")]`.
5. `App.axaml.cs` line count: currently 142 lines. Extracting a 10-line factory method + replacing 9 inline lines with 1 call adds ~1 net line, well under 300.

